The paper discusses anonymization of microdata, which is a common topic in the database community (cs.DB). It also introduces a new privacy model and discusses intruder models, which are common topics in the security and cryptography community (cs.CR). The paper also discusses utility and privacy metrics, which are common topics in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The paper also discusses transparency to users, which is a common topic in human-computer interaction and privacy (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses verifiability by subjects, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT).
